<section xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:lang="en-US" xml:id="geogebra-solving-inequalities-graphically-one">
  <title>Using a Graph to Solve an Inequality - Part I</title>

  <figure xml:id="geogebra-solving-inequalities-graphically-one-geogebra">
    <caption>The parabola is the function <m>f</m>.  Drag the button labeled "up/down" - umm... - up and down to change the problem and solution.</caption>
    <interactive platform="geogebra" width="100%" aspect="9:5">
      <slate surface="geogebra" aspect="9:5" source="geogebra/functions-less-than.ggb">
            setPerspective("G");
            setAxisSteps(1, 1, 1, 1);
            setCoordSystem(-8, 8, -2, 14);
            setGridVisible(1);         
            setAxisLabels(1,"x","y","z");
      </slate>
    </interactive>
  </figure>

</section>
